<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1600 GMT, September 13 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONDORF LES BAINS -- The EU finance ministers Saturday started
discussion on a global approach to taxation as a run-up to the
convergence for the European single currency.
</P>
<P>
The informal meeting was the first opportunity since April last
year for the finance ministers to develop cooperation at EU level
on taxation policy and on measures to curtail harmful tax
competition in the single market. (EU-Meeting-Taxation)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ROME -- Italy and France intend to work together on all leading
international issues, Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto Dini said
Friday after his talks with French Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a joint press conference, both Dini and Vedrine
accentuated the positive factors in bilateral relations and their
common intention to pursue "concrete actions" on European and
international problems. (Italy-France-Ties)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NAIROBI -- Mali's cabinet headed by Premier Ibrahim Boubacar
Keita have resigned in an attempt to solve a political crisis
resulted from the second multi-party national elections this year.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here Saturday from Bamako, capital of Mali
said, the news was made known by President Alpha Oumar Konare
Friday when he was meeting with the country's political
parties. (Mali-Premier Resigns)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French President Jacques Chirac said in the latest
issue of the German weekly "Focus" that a delay in the launching
of the European single currency, the euro, will be dangerous for
all.
</P>
<P>
"There is a date and it should be respected. Otherwise we risk
burying the single currency," said Chirac in an interview with
"Focus" which was published Saturday.
</P>
<P>
He said that a delay of euro will bring "very serious
consequences" to the market of exchange and the economy of many
countries, as well as "a deeper undermining than one can imagine"
of the European monetary union. (France-Chirac-Euro) 
</P>
</TEXT>
