<HEADLINE> Li Ju, Wang Nan Win Semi Berths in Women's World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 13 (Xinhua) -- World champion Li Ju and
Wang Nan of China booked semifinal berths in the women's singles
competition of the World Cup table tennis tournament here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Li beat compatriot Wang Chen 21-12, 21-17, 21-11, while Wang
defeated Jie Schoepp of Germany 21-16, 21-14, 21-13.
</P>
<P>
The other two semifinal berths went to Li Chunli of New Zealand
and Geng Lijuan of Canada.
</P>
<P>
Geng, who ranked 11th in the world, stunned 1988 Seoul Olympic
champion and fifth-ranked Chen Jing of Chinese Taipei 21-12,
21-12, 21-16.
</P>
<P>
The world 49-ranked Li Chunli also advanced with a surprise
victory, upseting 17-ranked Cha Po Wa of Hong Kong, China, 21-18,
22-20, 21-13. 
</P>
</TEXT>
