<HEADLINE> Three Killed in Washington Helicopter Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed
and five others injured when a helicopter carrying eight people
crashed Friday near Olympic National Park, northwestern Washington
State.
</P>
<P>
The Bell 205-A1 chopper, carrying a pilot and seven passengers,
was on a search mission for an elderly hiker who disappeared a
week ago near Mount Baldy.
</P>
<P>
It crashed at a site about 85 kilometers west of Seattle at
about 4 p.m. local time Friday.
</P>
<P>
The five injured people were sent to hospitals for medical
treatment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
