<HEADLINE> Air Zimbabwe to Increase Flights to London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Air Zimbabwe has reached an
agreement with two regional airlines to increase its weekly
flights to London.
</P>
<P>
Air Zimbabwe public relations manager David Mwenga today said
a tentative agreement had been reached with Aero-Zambia, whereby
air Zimbabwe would introduce a fifth flight to London via Lusaka.
</P>
<P>
He said an agreement with Air Malawi, expected to take effect
in February or March next year, would see Air Zimbabwe fly to
London via Lilongwe, making it the sixth weekly flight to the
destination.
</P>
<P>
He also denied that regional routes like Maputo, Beira and
Mbabane would face the axe due to low volumes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
