<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exhibition Shows Jilin a Fertile Land </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Under a red banner
proclaiming "Jilin People Congratulate the Opening of the 15th CPC
National Congress," hundreds of photographs, models and products
show the economic and social progress achieved in northeast
China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The display is part of the ongoing "Glorious Five Years"
national exhibit at the Beijing Exhibition Center, which showcases
the overall development in China since the convening of the 14th
CPC Naional Congress in 1992.
</P>
<P>
According to the display, grain output in Jilin increased from
18.4 million tons in 1992 to 23.26 million tons last year, and
among the country's top ten grain production counties, six are in
the province.
</P>
<P>
Automobile production, the petrochemicals industry,
pharmaceuticals and food processing have taken leads in local
economic growth. Last year, the China No.1 Auto Group, known as
the "cradle of China's auto industry", produced 233,000 cars,
bringing its sales volume up to 21.7 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The Jilin Oilfield continued to produce 3.5 million tons of
crude oil or more yearly for the past few years, ranking eighth
among China's on-land oil and gas fields.
</P>
<P>
Infrastructure construction has been well developed in the
region, with recent completion of a power plant with a total
installed capacity of 2.4 million kilowatt and a 133-km expressway.
</P>
<P>
Minority nationalities in the province get along well with the
Han people there, and one of its autonomous prefectures has been
designated by the State Council as a model of national unity.
</P>
<P>
The provincial government encourages its artists to produce
more outstanding works for Jilin residents, and 25 works have won
national awards since 1992. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
