<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambique to Increase Prawns Exports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Mozambique will export
some 7000 tonnes of prawns this year, a 16 percent increase over
1996, the deputy minister of agriculture and fisheries Izadora
Faztudo said today in Maputo.
</P>
<P>
Local media quoted the official as saying that the increase in
exports is possible because more reserves of prawns have been
identified.
</P>
<P>
She told a press conference that her government will allow
prawn fishing to continue right up to the end of December, and
possible into January.
</P>
<P>
The government is also reviewing prawn prices, in the hope of
increasing the amount of foreign exchange the resource brings
into the country.
</P>
<P>
Prawns now account for 41 percent of Mozambique's commodity
export earnings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
