<HEADLINE> PLC Supports Renewing Security Coop With Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Palestinian Legislative
Council (PLC) promised in Ramallah today to renew security
cooperation with Israel, Israeli Radio reported.
</P>
<P>
Following U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright's visit,
the PLC met in Ramallah today and discussed in detail about the
future security cooperation with Israel, the Radio said.
</P>
<P>
The PLC has expressed its support to security cooperation with
Israel, but at the same time said that it will accept neither
terrorism nor Israeli dictatorship.
</P>
<P>
During her three-day visit to Israel and Palestine which
concluded Friday, Albright stressed on several occasions the
importance of renewing security cooperation between Israel and
Palestinian National Authority (PNA), saying it is vital for
moving the Middle East peace process forward.
</P>
<P>
PNA and Israel have different explanations on security
cooperation. The Israeli side put much stress on PNA's fighting
against terrorism, while PNA asked Israel to implement the Oslo
accords and to discuss and solve practical issues between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
PNA President Yasser Arafat, during his talks with Albright in
Ramallah, promised to take strict actions against terrorism.
</P>
</TEXT>
