<HEADLINE> Western Africa Considers Forming a Sub-Regional </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS,September 13 (Xinhua) -- A conference will be held in
Nigerian capital Abuja from October 7 to 9 on the creation of a
sub-regional coastal shipping company for western and central
Africa.
</P>
<P>
The Nigeria Shippers Council (NSC) said in a statement in
Abuja today that the conference is part of the efforts aimed at
fine tuning the five-year-old plan for the creation of such a
firm.
</P>
<P>
C.N. Egonwokocha, NSC's Assistant Director for Public
Relations, said the conference would bring together potential
investors from the sub-region and institute a steering committee
comprising private investors to ultimately decide on the
constitution of the firm.
</P>
<P>
Potential investors, shipping agents and shipping lines in the
sub-region will attend the three-day meeting at the Abuja ECOWAS
(the Economic Community of West African States) secretariat, she
said.
</P>
<P>
The conference is jointly organized by the Ministerial
Conference of Western and Central African States on Maritime
Transport, the Economic Commission for Africa, ECOWAS and other
specialized agencies, the official added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
