<HEADLINE> EU to Announce Euro Rate Next May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONDORF LES BAINS, Luxembourg, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The
European Union is to announce the rate between the euro and the
currencies of the participating countries next May, it was
announced here today.
</P>
<P>
At a joint press conference with European Commission President
Jacques Santer, Luxembourg Prime Minister Jean-Claude Juncker,
whose country is serving the rotating presidency of the 15-nation
union, said the announcement will be made on the very day when the
list of the first batch of EU countries are chosen to join the
single currency.
</P>
<P>
EU's executive agency, the European Commission, is to sort out
the countries eligible to join the euro.
</P>
<P>
The timing of the announcement was believed to help prevent
speculative activities in the run-up to January 1, 1999, when the
euro is to be launched officially.
</P>
<P>
The press conference came after the end of an informal meeting
of EU finance ministers who discussed matters related to forging a
global approach toward a common taxation policy and taking
concrete measures to curtail harmful tax competition in the single
market.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, held at a Luxembourg town bordering France, was
presided over by Luxembourg which has made taxation one of its
main priorities during its six-month tenure of EU presidency.
</P>
<P>
The finance ministers last met in April 1996 at Verona, Italy,
and a consensus has since emerged on the key challenges to EU's
taxation policies. 
</P>
</TEXT>
