<HEADLINE> Qian Qichen on Peaceful Reunification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- One of the important parts
for holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory is to
promote the peaceful reunification of the motherland under the
great concept of "one country, two systems", Qian Qichen,
vice-premier and foreign minister, said here today.
</P>
<P>
Qian, a delegate to the on-going 15th National Party Congress,
made the remark in the panel discussion of the delegation from the
northeast China province of Jilin.
</P>
<P>
He said: "One country, two systems" has reflected the matter of
principle of China to accomplish the reunification of the
motherland and safeguard China's sovereignty while taking into
account the historical and current situations of Taiwan, Hong Kong
and Macao. It constitutes a basic principle in promoting peaceful
reunification of the motherland, he said.
</P>
<P>
"One country, two systems" not only is a theory but a theory in
practice with Hong Kong's return to the motherland becoming a
hallmark of a great success of the concept. It will be another
grand occasion when Macao returns to the motherland, he said.
</P>
<P>
Qian said Jiang Zemin renewed his solemn appeal in his report
to the congress that the two sides of the Straits can hold
negotiations and reach an agreement on "officially ending the
state of hostility between the two sides in accordance with the
principle that there is only one China."
</P>
<P>
"On the premise that there is only on China, we are prepared to
talk about any matter. All opinions and proposals can be put
forward as long as they are in the interests of the reunification.
The question of the reunification of the motherland should be
solved by us Chinese on both sides of the Taiwan Straits," Qian
Qichen quoted Jiang Zemin as saying.
</P>
<P>
"We are determined and confident and we can realize the
peaceful reunification of the motherland," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
