<HEADLINE> Italy Tops Karate World Cup With Four Golds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Italy dominated the 6th Karate
World Cup by grabbing four gold medals, three silvers and four
bronzes in the four-day tournament which ended here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
France finished second with three golds and one silver while
Britain came in third with three golds but no silver and bronze.
</P>
<P>
Charestella Bux beat Gorda Casanova of Spain 3-2 in the women's
open kumite to give Italy its fourth and final title on
Sunday. Her teammate, Roberta Minett, took the bronze.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Italy snatched the gold in the team kata event,
defeating the Philippines and Indonesia, which settled for the
silver and the bronze, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Frenchman Cristophe Pinna, scoring 3-1-0 against his
compatriot, Gilles Cherdieu, won the man's open kumite. Celik of
Turkey and Takao Kame of Japan settled for the bronze.
</P>
<P>
The Manila competition attracted some 342 players from 43
countries and regions. It will be last World Karate Cup staged by
the World Karate Federation because it plans to concentrate on the
World Karate Championships in future competitions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
