<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exposition on Primary Stage of Socialism Clears Up Misgivings (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ni Zhenliang, secretary of Doudian Village Party Committee in
rural Beijing, said that the reason why they suffered in
developing the rural economy in the past few years was they
deviated from the actual conditions in rural China.
</P>
<P>
"The reason behind the success in rural economic restructuring
was the correct understanding of the primary stage of socialism
and our concentrated efforts to emancipate and develop productive
forces," he added.
</P>
<P>
Li Wenhai, president of People's University of China, said:
"Only by having a better understanding of national conditions and
grasping the basic features of the primary stage of socialism, can
we work out the correct principles and policies guiding economic
development and social progress."
</P>
<P>
Referring to some people saying that a century is too long for
the primary stage of socialism, Zhang Haoruo, vice minister of
the State Commission for Economic Restructuring, said, "we would
rather keep it longer. Otherwise, we would commit the mistake of
hastiness."
</P>
<P>
Lu Gongxun, chairman of the Standing Committee of the Shanxi
Provincial People's Congress, said one of the root causes for the
mistakes committed in building socialism prior to the Third
Plenary Session of the 11th Central Committee in the late 1978
resulted in the fact that the policies we had made leaped over the
primary stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Wan Fumin, secretary of Haicheng City Party Committee in
Liaoning, said that different contradictions exist in China's
economy, politics, culture, social activities and other areas in
the primary stage of socialism. But the principal contradiction is
the one between the growing material and cultural needs of the
people and the backwardness of production.
</P>
<P>
This principal contradiction will remain throughout the primary
stage of socialism in China and in all aspects of social life.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
