<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Exposition on Primary Stage of Socialism Clears Up Misgivings (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Delegates to the ongoing 15th
National Party Congress shared the same view that stressing the
primary stage of socialism provides a guarantee for China's reform
and opening-up has laid a foundation for solving various
contraditions and clearing up misgivings.
</P>
<P>
Xie Fei, secretary of the Guangdong Provincial Committee of the
Communist Party of China, said that "the birth of Deng Xiaoping
Theory was the fruit of emancipating the mind and seeking thuth
from facts."
</P>
<P>
"We should solve problems facing us from the actual conditions
which boil down that we are still in the primary stage of
socialism," he said, adding that "if we fail to do so, it would be
difficult for us crack the hard nuts in restructuring, such as
readjusting the structure of the ownership."
</P>
<P>
The diversified form of public ownership and the combination of
the distribution principle "to each according to one's work and
the basic means of production are also the result of emancipating
the mind and seeking truth from facts, he added.
</P>
<P>
Wan Yongxiang, Chinese ambassador to the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, said the nine-feature exposition of the primary
stage of socialism in Jing Zemin's report to the five-yearly
congress illustrated the principle of seeking truth from facts.
</P>
<P>
Shi Dazhen, minister of Power Industry, said the report gives a
full account of the theory of the primary stage of socialism.
"Guided by the theory, we can avoid setbacks in reforms and
opening-up and big ups-and-downs in economic development," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Wang Xiaofeng, deputy secretary of the Hainan Provincial
Committee, said the theory on the primary stage of socialism, put
forward since the Third Plenary Session of the 11th Central
Committee, "is scientific and accords with the actual conditions
of China and the development of the history of the mankind."
</P>
<P>
This is because the productive forces should be developed stage
by stage, and the primary stage of socialism could not be leaped
over, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970914.0054 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Calls for Correct Understanding of Jiang's Report (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Zhu Rongji has described the
report delivered by Jiang Zemin at the opening session of the
15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) as
"epoch-making."
</P>
<P>
The report holds high the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory, and
achieves progress in some respects, said Zhu in a panel discussion
with delegates from Shaanxi province on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the report has summarized the experience
accumulated in reforms and development over the past few years.
</P>
<P>
Zhu expressed his sincere support to the report.
</P>
<P>
Regarding the issue of ownership, Zhu thought that the report
offers a distinct answer in this regard.
</P>
<P>
The report has upheld the basic principles of Marxism-Leninism
and solved new problems in the historical process, Zhu said. "This
is of great significance for creating a new situation in the cause
of building socialism with Chinese characteristics," he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu called for objective analysis of the fact that proportion
of the non-public sector to the national economy is increasing.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that the public sector includes not only the state-
and collectively-owned sectors, but also the state- and
collectively-owned elements in the sector of mixed ownership.
</P>
<P>
Zhu also pointed out that there are state and
collectively-owned shares in all the joint ventures across the
country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970914.0055 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Calls for Correct Understanding of Jiang's Report (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
"To revitalize the state enterprises," Zhu said,"we still have
to stick to the principle of managing well large enterprises while
adopting a flexible policy toward small ones."
</P>
<P>
"If these 1,000 enterprises have good performance, the whole
country will promise high hopes of success," he said.
</P>
<P>
There are many ways to deal with small enterprises, one of
which is to introduce joint stock partnership, Zhu said. he also
called for support for the partnership.
</P>
<P>
"Whatever partnership is introduced, labor cooperation or
capital cooperation, once the small enterprises cooperate with one
another, they will be enlivened," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Zhu said that support and correct guidance should be
given to joint stock partnership. He also cautioned people against
"rushing headlong into mass action," saying that the partnership
cannot be implemented through administrative orders or by forcing
workers to buy shares.
</P>
<P>
Zhu noted that shareholding system is not a compulsory way in
state enterprises, nor is joint stock partnership the only way for
small enterprises. "I always have said shareholding is not a
panacea," he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu called for correct and comprehensive understanding and
implementation of the report, which he described as "an integral
whole."
</P>
<P>
The urgent task for the national economy at present is to
accelerate the reform of state-owned enterprises, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970914.0056 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Calls for Correct Understanding of Jiang's Report (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At present, Zhu said, joint ventures constitute the overwhelming
majority of the foreign-funded enterprises, while the number of
wholly foreign-funded enterprises is very small.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that the state and collective have held the
controlling share in quite a number of joint ventures. Hence,
public ownership has retained its dominant position, he added.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that enterprises like these obviously have the
characteristics of public ownership, and are favorable to
expanding the area of control by public capital.
</P>
<P>
"Enterprises in this category cannot be considered completely
non-public enterprises," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
"The dominant role of the state sector of the economy is mainly
manifested in its controlling power," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Now that the state-owned sector still holds a firm grasp of
the economic lifelines of the country, Zhu said, and hence there
is no risk to develop the non-public sector.
</P>
<P>
Explaining why China should develop diverse forms ownership side
by side, Zhu said that China is currently in the primary stage of
socialism.
</P>
<P>
"Developing the non-public sector according to the principle of
'three favorables' brings about only benefits," he said.
</P>
<P>
The volume of profit and tax handed over by the 1,000
state-owned large-and-medium enterprises, which enjoyed
priority support from the government, currently take up 85
percent of total of the country, Zhu said, adding that this also
shows the dominant position of the state enterprises.
</P>
</TEXT>
