<HEADLINE> Dhaka Approves 11 Projects Involving 300 Million Dollars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Committee of
National Economic Council (ECNEC) of Bangladesh today approved 11
projects involving an estimated amount of 13.20 billion taka
(about 300 million U.S. dollars), Bangladesh Sangbad Sangstha
(BSS) reported this evening.
</P>
<P>
Among the approved projects are a "western region gas project",
a power plant rehabilitation, procurement of 200-double deck
passenger carriers, procurement of most modern hydraulic composite
garbage removing trucks and construction of a poverty alleviation
training complex, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
The other schemes approved by the ECNEC included the Asian
Development Bank (ADB) financed over 1.5 billion taka (about 34
million dollars) participatory project for livestock development,
an interim project for improvement of water supply situation and a
crude oil storage tank construction project, BSS stated.
</P>
<P>
The funds for all the 11 projects have already been procured,
BSS added.  
</P>
