<HEADLINE> Bahraini PM on Genuine Peace in Mideast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Bahraini Prime Minister Sheikh
Khalifa Ben Salman said a genuine peace in the Middle East should
be based on balance of power and restoration of legitimate rights
of all.
</P>
<P>
In an exclusive interview published by Egyptian newspaper
"Al-Ahram" today, the prime minister pointed out that it is
impossible to achieve peace by putting pressure on one party in
favor of the other.
</P>
<P>
"We cannot be optimistic about the future of the Middle East
peace process with regard to the existing volatile atmosphere and
the refusal by head of the Israeli government to honor his
obligations in accordance with the peace agreements concluded,"
Sheikh Khalifa Ben Salman said.
</P>
<P>
"What is happening at present is contrary to all the agreements
the Palestinians and Israelis have come to," he said. "Those
constant pressures exerted by the Israelis on both the Palestinian
National Authority Chairman Yasser Arafat and the Palestinian
people would not serve the peace process so much as they would
cause the situation to explode."
</P>
<P>
Stressing the importance of inter-Arab cooperation, Sheikh
Khalifa Ben Salman said that genuine Arab solidarity originates
from serious economic cooperation intended to achieve prosperity
for the Arab people.
</P>
<P>
He called on Arab states to scrap customs barriers between
them and to change their economic systems so as to make it
possible for an Arab common market to come into being.
</P>
<P>
Sheikh Khalifa Ben Salman is due to visit Egypt heading a
high-ranking delegation on September 16. 
</P>
</TEXT>
