<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Oil Refinery Fire in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- At least two people died
and several others were injured today in a big fire at an oil
refinery in southern India, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
The reports said that the blaze started in the pipeline
connecting the refinery owned by the Hindustan Petroleum
Corporation Limited (HPCL) with the southeastern port of
Visakhapatam in Andhra Pradesh.
</P>
<P>
The nearby seven storage tanks also caused fire and
firefighting units were battling the inferno.
</P>
<P>
The entire pipeline area has been cordoned off. Two relief
camps in the city have been set up for the people fleeing the
industrial township.  
</P>
