<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Zambian former president
Kenneth Kaunda has flown to South Africa for treatment of
gun-shot wounds he sustained when police fired live bullets to
disperse an oppotion rally last month.
</P>
<P>
A local newspaper Sunday Mail today quoted an unnamed official
of Kaunda's United National Independece Party (UNIP) as saying
