<HEADLINE> Team SCRA Claims Title of Outdoor Quest in Xichang </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XICHANG, Sichuan Province, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Team Santa
Cruz Adventure Racers held off a last-minute challenge form Team
Eco-Internet to claim the title of the inaugural Mild Seven
Outdoor Quest which concluded Xichang of Sichuan province,
Southwest China, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The Team SCAR clocked three hours seven minutes and 40 seconds
in the fourth and final day's racing, collecting a overall winning
time of 18:29:19 for the title of the 17-team event.
</P>
<P>
Overnight leader Team Eco-Internet finished the day in 3:13:02
to fall into the second place in 18:27:25. And team Photon Red
Bull came into the third spot in 19:32:26.
</P>
<P>
The Xichang outdoor quest is a four-day 250-km multisport stage
race. The team with the lowest overall time over the four days
wins the title.
</P>
<P>
Each team consists of four individuals who race together,
contesting seven outdoor endurance sports of trail running,
mountain biking, offroad inline skating, mountain bike biathlon,
Mountaineering, lake paddling and river paddling. 
</P>
