<HEADLINE> Armed forces Cut Wins Support from China's Diplomats (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin's announcement of
reducing the Chinese armed forces by 500,000 in the next three
years has won universal support from China's diplomat-delegates
and military officers attending the current five-yearly Party
Congress.
</P>
<P>
They held that the decision was made on the basis of the
changes in international situation and on the actual conditions of
the country and the army.
</P>
<P>
It also benefits the country's modernization drive with
economic construction as the center and accords with the global
trend of peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said the cut of armed forces
proved that China follows a defensive and peaceful strategy.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, he said, some countries spread the so-called
"China threat." "The decison on armed forces cut has once again
illustrated China's sincerity and its independent foreign policy
of peace, and smashed the rumors," he pointed out.
</P>
<P>
"Now, people can draw only one conclusion that China is a
peace-loving country viewed either politically, or economically or
diplomatically, or in term of national defense," the vice-minister
said, quoting the relevant statements in Jiang's report.
</P>
<P>
China has always dedicated to world peace and development and
the "China threat" fallacy is not tenable, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970914.0076 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Armed Forces Cut Wins Support From China's Diplomats (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhao Taizhong, political commissar of the Nanjing Military Area
Command, said that "the key to improve the army building and the
national defense lies in quality instead of quantity only."
</P>
<P>
The only correct road China should take is to have fewer but
better troops and arm them through science and technology, he
added.
</P>
<P>
"If the reduction of armed forces by one million in the 1980s
was the wise decision of the late Chinese leader Deng Xiaoping,
the armed forces cut by 500,000 in the next three years is the
wise decision of the Party Central Committee and the Central
Military Commission with Jiang Zemin at the core," said Zhao who
has served in the army for 35 years.
</P>
<P>
The disarmament this time shows the confidence and
determination of the third generation of China's central leading
collective with Jiang Zemin as the core to promote world peace, he
added.
</P>
<P>
Jing Zhiyuan, an officer of the Second Artillery Corps, said
the purpose of improving the quality of the PLA and taking the
road of fewer but better troops is to raise the defense capability
of China.
</P>
<P>
"Improvement of the army building requires a shift from
expansion of scale to improvement of quality and efficiency and
from a personnel-intensive to technology-intensive development,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
The 53-year-old officer stressed that the key to improving
the army building is to raise the combat effectiveness of troops.
</P>
<P>
He believes that the establishment of the army units would
become more rational and their combat effectiveness would be
raised after the disarmament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
