<HEADLINE> Congress Delegate on Theoretical Breakthroughs of Jiang's Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Theoretical breakthroughs in
the congress report regarding the issue of ownership will provide
a great impetus to economic restructuring, said Ren Zhongyi, a
delegate from south China's Guangdong Province, here today.
</P>
<P>
Joining other Guangdong delegates to the congress in a panel
discussion, Ren, former secretary of the province's Party
committee, said, "I agree with and support the report" delivered
by Jiang Zemin at the 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China, which opened on Friday.
</P>
<P>
He said the new characteristics and major contributions of the
report are mainly reflected in the fact that it declares that Deng
Xiaoping Theory will be written into the Constitution of the
Party.
</P>
<P>
"It has immeasurable significance over various undertakings of
the Party and the socialist cause in the future," Ren said.
</P>
<P>
It is extremely important that the report has reiterated and
emphasized that China remains in the primary stage of socialism,
and that the stage is to last at least a hundred years, said Ren.
</P>
<P>
In the past decades, questions like what socialism is and how
it will be built were not fullly understood, he said. Due to the
lack of experience, it was once widely believed that it needn't
take long to realize communism. And consequently we had done
something against the law of history, he added.
</P>
<P>
"We should draw a lesson from this," said Ren.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that the report has pointed out more
connotations of the public sector of the economy and its status,
affirming that public ownership should take diversified forms.
</P>
<P>
The major breakthroughs will give a push to the overall
economic restructuring, economic development and even the
deepening of political restructuring, Ren pointed out.
</P>
<P>
He said the report has pointed out that the shareholding system
cannot be simply labeled public or private, and that joint stock
partnership can be introduced in socialist countries, and that
remuneration according to work and remuneration according to
factors of production should be combined.
</P>
<P>
The new breakthroughs are resulted from the party's
implementation of the ideological line of emancipating the mind
and seeking truth from facts, said Ren. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
