<HEADLINE> Premier Stresses Relations with Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng today
emphasized the importance of Africa and reaffirmed China's
consistent support for African nations.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Kojo Tsikata, national security advisor
and member of the State Council of Ghana, Li said that Africa, a
major component of developing countries, is a continent with great
development potential and hope.
</P>
<P>
Li stressed that China has consistently supported African
nations in their just struggle for safeguarding independence,
sovereignty and national integrity, as well as their economic
development, and appropriate demands and rational proposals
concerning international affairs.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China and Ghana have maintained long-term
cooperation and have maintained friendly contacts in political,
economic, cultural and military fields.
</P>
<P>
China is happy to see that Ghana has adopted its own
development strategy in accordance with the existing domestic
situation and the interests of its people.
</P>
<P>
Li said that Ghana's efforts have stimulated the nation's
economy, upgraded the living standards of the people, and
contributed to peace, stability and economic growth of Africa, and
to the peace of the world as a whole.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that China and Ghana share many things in
common, and that China is grateful for Ghana's consistent support
on issues related to Taiwan, human rights, and China's membership
in the World Trade Organization.
</P>
<P>
Tsikata offered congratulations on the convening of the 15th
National Congress of the Chinese Communist Party.
</P>
<P>
He said the fact that China has rendered considerable support
and unselfish aid to the just cause of the people of Ghana fully
demonstrates the nation's strong solidarity and close cooperation
with African countries. Tsikata pointed out that the Chinese
people are the most reliable friends of the African people.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
