<HEADLINE> Sino-US MBA Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- China's Qinghua University
and the Massachusetts Institute of Technology from the United
States joined in ceremonies here today to mark the inauguration of
a new MBA program at one of China's most prestigious universities.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua has enrolled the program's first class of 40 students
who passed nationwide entrance examinations and special English
language skills tests.
</P>
<P>
The agreement between the two institutes of higher education
call for Qinghua to send 20 people to United States for further
MBA training over the next five years. The students are scheduled
to complete the course and return to China to teach the jointly
sponsored course.
</P>
<P>
China's implementation of the policy of reform and opening has
created an increasing need for senior business managers, according
to Qinghua Professor Li Zinai.
</P>
<P>
Li also pointed out that the unique aspect of China's stock
markets require the services of people with special training.
</P>
<P>
Qinghua, which offers the most extensive MBA education in
China, has granted a total of 147 MBA degrees since 1991, with
some 700 students currently enrolled in the program. 
</P>
</TEXT>
