<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Library to Be Upgraded with Digital Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 14 (Xinhua) -- The provincial library in
northeast China's Liaoning Province will become the first
digitalized library in China.
</P>
<P>
The five-million-yuan system will be designed and engineered by
a local software company using IBM's popular library
digitalization package.
</P>
<P>
The system will be used to create an electronic databank on all
the books, magazines, newspapers and video cassettes in the
library. Readers use the databank to gain access to ancient books
which formerly were off limits to the public because libraries
feared they would be damaged.
</P>
<P>
The system will also link the library with other computer
networks for information sharing.
</P>
<P>
The Liaoning Library, with more than 3.1 million books in its
collection, is the largest public library in northeast China.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
