<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India Needs More Import of Oil in Next 5 Years </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- India's crude oil imports
are estimated to record an over 66 percent increase in the next
five years, Press Trust of India (PTI) said here today.
</P>
<P>
In the process, India's oil import dependence will go up from
60 percent now to 70 percent in the Ninth Five-Year Plan period
(1998-2002), necessitating import of 83 million tons of oil
equivalent in the terminal year of the plan from about 50 million
tons of oil equivalent in 1996-97.
</P>
<P>
The oil demand in India in the next five years will shoot up
from 83.9 million tons of oil equivalent to 120 million tons,
whereas domestic production would grow marginally from 33.87
million tons to 37 million tons.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
