<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-14 10:56 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 2 Israeli Soldiers Killed in S. Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Two Israeli soldiers were
killed in South Lebanon overnight in a roadside bombing launched
by Hezbollah guerrilla fighters, Israeli Army said today.
</P>
<P>
An Army statement said the two killed were among a foot
patrol squad in the central sector of the Israeli self-claimed
South Lebanon Security Zone. One soldier was killed at the
scene, another fatally wounded and died later on the way to the
hospital, a third soldier was lightly injured.
</P>
<P>
It said that the roadside bomb was detonated by Hezbollah
gunmen using remote control device. Army investigators have began
a probe into the incident.
</P>
<P>
The latest deaths brought to 33 the death toll of Israeli
soldiers killed in action in the security zone since the
beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
Israeli Cabinet, which convened its weekly session this
morning, reviewed the incident and current tension in South
Lebanon that threatens to escalate the confrontation.
</P>
<P>
On Friday night, an Israeli elite hit squad killed four
Hezbollah gunmen in an operation in the security zone, including
18-year-old Hadi Nasrallah, the son of Hezbollah leader Sheikh
Hassan Nasrallah.
</P>
<P>
Israeli soldiers brought back two bodies of Hezbollah gunmen,
including Hadi Nasrallah, which would be buried in Israel.
</P>
<P>
Israeli officials said that they expected to use the bodies
for an exchange for the body of Itamar Ilya, who was killed with
12 other officers on September 5 in an ambush by Hezbollah
gunmen duing a naval commando raid outside the security zone.
</P>
<P>
But Sheikh Nasrallah has vowed not to let Israel to exploit
the killing of his son, saying "thanks God for making my son a
martyr." He told a rally that Hezbollah fighters were willing to
sacrifice their lives to free their land from Israeli occupation.
</P>
<P>
The death of Nasrallah's son is expected to spark a new round
of revenge attacks against Israeli targets by Hezbollah gunmen,
which will escalate the high tension in South Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
