<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Government Asked to Drop Dual Fare Structure </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Officials in India's
tourism sector have urged the government to drop the dual fare
structure in the aviation sector for international tourists in
order to give a push to the tourist industry.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a one-day conference on tourism and travel here
today, they said that the dual fare structure of collecting air
fares from foreign tourists in rupee and US dollars was being
looked upon with suspicion as the US dollar rates are higher than
equivalent rupee structure.
</P>
<P>
They said that foreign tourists coming to India will have to
pay much more than the locals when they travel in the country by
air. Such a dual fare structure does not exist in the railway
sector.
</P>
<P>
A lot of complaints have been heard from foreign tourists and
the dual fare system has hurt India's tourism, they said.
</P>
<P>
Participants in the conference also suggested that immigration
and customs clearance procedure should be made easier and faster
for foreign tourists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
