<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0800 GMT, September 14 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO -- A free trade agreement will be signed by the
European Union (EU) and Southern Common Market (Mercosur) in 1999,
European Commission (EC) Vice President Manuel Marin said on
Friday.
</P>
<P>
Marin said that the agreement, to be signed at the first Latin
American-European Union Summit scheduled for 1999 in Rio de
Janeiro, will be the last of a two-stage process that began
December 1995 when the two regions signed a political and economic
cooperation accord in Madrid. The two blocs also proposed to
establish a free trade area, the largest one in the world, before
2005. (EU-Mercosur-Accord)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ZAGREB -- Polling stations opened at 07:00 a.m. Saturday to 2.5
million Bosnian-Herzegovinian voters in two-day municipal
elections, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Ninety one political parties joined the elections, running for
their seats in a total of 136 municipalities, whose results are
expected by September 20. The elections are being followed by
2,450 supervisors from 39 countries of the Organization on
Security and Cooperation in Europe and by 300 other international
supervisors. (Bosnia-Municipal Poll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
