<HEADLINE> Party's Guiding Ideology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- It is "the aspiration of the
whole Party as well as the 4.2 million people in Deng Xiaoping's
hometown to establish Deng's theory as the guiding ideology of the
Party in its Constitution," a congress delegate said here
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a panel discussion, Luo Songbai, Party secretary of
the Guang'An Prefecture, the native town of Deng Xiaoping in
southwest China's Sichuan Province, noted that the Party central
committee has proposed that the current Party congress
establishes Deng Xiaoping Theory as the guiding ideology of the
Communist Party of China in its Constitution.
</P>
<P>
Having worked in Guang'An for more than two decades, Luo
witnessed the historic changes in this birthplace of Deng's since
China introduced the policy of reforms and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
"The place used to be very poor due to frequent natural
adversities," Luo said, adding that local people could not have
enough to eat in poor years.
</P>
<P>
"The theory of Deng Xiaoping on building socialism with Chinese
characteristics has worked a miracle in his hometown," Luo told
his fellow delegates.
</P>
<P>
In 1993, Guang'An was upgraded from a county to a prefecture
and embarked on a "fast lane" of development guided by Deng's
directive that economic development is the first priority.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the gross domestic product (GDP) of Guang'An
increased by 42 percent compared with the figure in 1993. The per
capita output of grain and annual net income kept going up for
four consecutive years with the 1996 per capita grain out reaching
500 kg and that of net income climbing to 1,800 yuan,respectively,
more than eight times the 1993 figures.
</P>
<P>
"Straw-roofed huts are gone in Guang'an," Luo said.
</P>
<P>
"The fellow villagers of Deng Xiaoping will never forget his
signal contributions," Luo said.
</P>
<P>
"Though the great man has gone, but the great banner of Deng
Xiaoping Theory has already been held high by the Party Central
Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core," he said.
</P>
<P>
"This great banner has taken roots in the hearts of his fellow
villagers, and we would live up to his great expectations and turn
his wish of 'making Guang'An prosperous' into reality," he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
