<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Delegates of Taiwan Origin Expect Cross-Strait Reunification </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Delegates of Taiwan origin
attending the on-going 15th national Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) are confident of realizing peaceful
reunification of the motherland in the near future of the next
century.
</P>
<P>
They were deeply touched by the fact that there is a special
part in Jiang Zemin's report dealing with promoting the peaceful
reunification of the motherland.
</P>
<P>
Lin Liyun, an advisor to the All-China Federation of Taiwan
Compatriots (ACFTC), said that she noted the moment when a long
and warm applause punctuated Jiang Zemin's statement while
delivering his report: "With full determination, we are capable of
finding a final solution to the Taiwan question.... the complete
reunification of the motherland and the all-round rejuvenation of
the Chinese nation will certainly come true."
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong and its development after July 1 have
made our Taiwan compatriots to be more confident of the future,"
she said.
</P>
<P>
Lee Teng-hui and his like can not turn the general trend of
realizing the reunification, she added. Taiwan will enjoy a
sustainable and stable economic growth so long as it combines its
future development with that in the interior areas, she said.
</P>
<P>
Yang Guoqing, vice president of the ACFTC, said that Hong
Kong's return to the embrace of the motherland has created a
favorable condition for the solution of Taiwan issue.
</P>
<P>
Facts have shown, he added, the principle of "one country, two
systems" is a scientific conclusion and has been proved to be
entirely practicable.
</P>
<P>
The tendency of splittism in the island in recent years has
hindered the progress of the cause of peaceful reunification.
Nevertheless, he said, "we must solve the Taiwan issue in line
with the principle of "one country, two systems," he stressed.
</P>
<P>
China's basic principle on solving the Taiwan issue and the
eight-point proposition on developing the cross-strait relations
will remain unchanged, he said.
</P>
<P>
Any attempt to separate Taiwan from the motherland will doom to
failure, Yang said.
</P>
<P>
Being a native of Taiwan of the second generation, Chen Weiwen
expects to contribute to the promotion of bilateral cooperation
between the two sides of the Taiwan Straits.
</P>
<P>
"I have many relatives in Taiwan, and this encourages me to do
something special for promoting the peaceful reunification," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Sun Guifen, a councillor of the ACFTC, said that the statement
of peaceful reunification in Jiang's report respects the history,
reality and the fundamental interests of Taiwan compatriots, who
are the mainstay to promote the peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Ke Lianmei, vice president of the ACFTC, said the interior
areas of China is the home of 34,000 Taiwan compatriots, 8,000 of
whom live in Fujian, which faces Taiwan island.
</P>
<P>
More than 4,800 Taiwan-funded firms have been built in Fujian,
suggesting the bilateral cooperation is an irreversible trend, he
added.
</P>
<P>
The Taiwan delegation has eight members, three of whom are
natives of Taiwan with the remainders the descendants of Taiwan
compatriots. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
