<HEADLINE> Graf to Skip Masters Tennis Tournament </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 13 (Xinhua) -- German Steffi Graf said on
Saturday that she would skip the New York Masters because of an
early operation to her knee.
</P>
<P>
The former world number one player said in a German TV program
that expectations for her early return is "unrealistic".
</P>
<P>
Graf, seven-times Wimbledon champion, said she would not put
her career in danger by attempting for a hurry return although she
had been guaranteed a wild card entry to the December event.
</P>
<P>
In June, Graf had an operation to her injuried knee and had
missed all the major events since then.
</P>
<P>
Graf, currently ranked just seventh in the world, was still
nursing her recovery in Austria.
</P>
<P>
"It's been a very long break this time and I'm looking more at
the Australian Open as my real comeback objective," said Graf.
</P>
