<HEADLINE> Colombia Requests OAS Presence in Local Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The Colombian
government has requested the Organization of American States (OAS)
to send international observers to supervise local elections on
October 26, the Foreign Ministry said today.
</P>
<P>
In a letter to OAS Secretary-General Cesar Gaviria, Colombian
Foreign Minister Maria Ema Mejia said "President Ernesto Samper
has reiterated that the National Electoral Council supports the
presence of international observers to ensure clean elections" in
the country.
</P>
<P>
Colombia will begin local elections of mayors, councilmen,
deputies and governors in municipalities and departments on
October 26.
</P>
<P>
The Colombian minister said the National Electoral Council
regarded it necessary for international observers to evaluate the
characteristics of electoral procedures, especially the design of
electoral census, the casting of votes and the scrutinies.
</P>
<P>
She asked the international group to defend equal political
rights of all parties, movements and candidates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
