platform diving title at the 10th World Cup diving competition
here on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
This was the fifth gold medal won by the Chinese divers as the
tournament went to its fourth day competition at Francisco Marquez
Olympic pool.
</P>
<P>
German Alexander Gorski and Heiko Meyer finished second in
299.46 points, while Alberto Acosta and Francisco Perez awarded
the host the first medal by finishing third in 297.75 points.
</P>
<P>
In the women's three-meter springboard event, Canadian Eryn
Bulmer took the gold medal in 333.45 points, beating Russian Yulia
Pakhalina to second in 333.33 points and Chinese Shi Lei finished
third in 326.76 points. 
