ZAGREB -- Polling stations opened at 07:00 am Saturday to 2.5
million Bosnian-Herzegovinian voters in two-day municipal
elections, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Ninety one political parties are running for their seats in a
total of 136 municipalities.
</P>
<P>
The elections are being followed by 2,450 supervisors from 39
countries of the Organization on Security and Cooperation in
Europe (OSCE) and by another 300 international supervisors. U.S.
special envoy for the Dayton peace accords' implementation Robert
Gelbard, who arrived in Sarajevo on Friday evening, will also
supervise the voting.
</P>
<P>
----
</P>
<P>
TUNIS, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The body of former Zairean
President Mobutu Sese Seko, who died six days ago, was buried
Saturday at the European Cemetery in the Moroccan capital of Rabat.
</P>
<P>
According to a report monitored here today, the funeral was
attended only by Mobutu's family members and a mass for him which
was planned to be held at the St. Peter Cathedral in Rabat was
canceled.
</P>
<P>
Mobutu, 66, died of prostate carcinoma last Sunday at King
Mohammed the Second Military Hospital in Rabat.
</P>
