<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Italy and Germany hope to
strengthen their military cooperation in technology and common
strategy within the framework of NATO, Italian and German defense
ministers said today.
</P>
<P>
In their talks in Venice, Italian Defense Minister Beniamino
Andreatta and his German counterpart Volker Ruhe focused on the
presence of Italian and German officers in partner nations at
various levels.
</P>
<P>
