Andreatta said he and Ruhe were confident that the problems
arising from the NATO expansion in the Madrid meeting would be
resolved. They also hoped the Mediterranean problems involving in
Greece and Turkey could be overcome in the next meeting of NATO in
December.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers reviewed the common industrial projects Italy
and Germany are working on, including the "Euro-fighter," which
Andreatta described as "the greatest European military-industrial
project in the next 15 years." 
