<HEADLINE> Russia Wins World Women's Youth Volleyball Championship </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WARSAW, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The Russian spikers outwitted
their Italian peers in a tough game to take the title of the ninth
World Women's Youth Volleyball Championship in Gdansk on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Russians savored the victory by downing the Italians 15-3,
15-8, 8-15, 4-15 and 16-14.
</P>
<P>
By taking the first set with ease in 20 minutes, the Russians
were ready for their celebration before the Italians rallied back
with perfect serves, strong spikes and tight defense to level the
scoreboard 2-2 in another 25 minutes.
</P>
<P>
In the decider wherein each serve scores one point for either
side, the Russians outwitted their peers with less unforced errors
for their final victory.
</P>
<P>
In the third-place playoff, China beat Japan in straight sets
for the bronze medals 15-0, 15-8 and 15-9, while Poland finished
fifth following a 3-0 win over the Czech Republic, and Germany
outscored Cuba 3-1 for a seventh-place finish, forcing Cuba to
tail in the eight-team tournament. 
</P>
