<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica's anti-drug
police have confiscated 277 kilos of cocaine in two recent
operations in the border zone with Panama, the Security Ministry
announced today.
</P>
<P>
Police searched a truck and found 77 kilos of cocaine in the
border port of Paso Canoas on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, police also seized 200 kilos of cocaine hidden in a
truck in the same area.
</P>
<P>
Both trucks came from Panama and were bound for Guatemala.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica's police have confiscated 1,874 kilos of cocaine in
the first eight months of this year. 
