<HEADLINE> Moya Faces Spanish Compatriot in Bournemouth Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 13 (Xinhua) -- Carlos Moya ousted Greg
Rusedski on Saturday for an all-Spaniard final at the Bournemouth
International Open tennis tournament.
</P>
<P>
The top seed Moya stopped Rusedski's run of success by winning
the late semifinal 6-2, 6-2 in merely 49 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The Briton who was born in Canada, reached the U.S. Open final
last week, was clearly out of his form as Moya roamed the court
with top-spun groundstrokes.
</P>
<P>
The Spanish world number five broke serve in the fifth game to
love and Rusedski's frustration began to show.
</P>
<P>
Moya surged ahead for a 4-0 lead in the second before Rusedski
held his serve for 1-4 but three games later a backhand floated
beyond the baseline, giving Moya the victory as expected.
</P>
<P>
The win set up an all-Spanish final in the tournament after
second seed Felix Mantilla eliminated South African Marcos
Ondruska 6-7, 6-1, 6-1 in the other semifinal. 
