<HEADLINE> World Games of Nature To Be Held in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 13 (Xinhua) -- The World Games of
Nature will be held from September 27 to Octobe 5 in the souther
Brazilian State of Parana.
</P>
<P>
The Parana State Sports Secretariat said that some 1,000
athletes from the five continents will take part in the games.
</P>
<P>
The World Games of Nature is a kind of Olympiad that includes
water, land, and air sports.
</P>
<P>
The games has three modalities: in the air, ballooning and
parachuting; in water, fishing and sailing; on land cyclism,
mountain climbing, golf, horsemanship, bow and arrow shooting, and
triathlon, among others.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, the International Olympic Committee set up an
environment commission to encourage sports dedicated to the
conservation of nature. 
</P>
</TEXT>
